Question:
====================Question====================
                    
Study the each pair of expressions given in Expressions column and match them with appropriate operator present in Relations column
                    
\[
        \begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|}
        \hline
        \text{ } & \text{Operations} & \text{ } & \text{Relations} \\ 
        \hline
        a & 1*11,15-4 & 1 & =  \\
        \hline
        b & 2-8,15-10 & 2 & < \\
        \hline
        c & 4*15,6-1 & 3 & >  \\ 
        \hline
        \end{array}
        \]
Solution_text:
Evaluate each pair of equation and compare it by doing so you will get solution for each pair as follows-
In expressions - $1*11,15-4$
$LHS = 1*11 = 11$
$RHS = 15-4 = 11$
$LHS = RHS$
In expressions - $2-8,15-10$
$LHS = 2-8 = -6$
$RHS = 15-10 = 5$
$LHS < RHS$
In expressions - $4*15,6-1$
$LHS = 4*15 = 60$
$RHS = 6-1 = 5$
$LHS > RHS$

Thus the correct option is - a-1 b-2 c-3
